YG HR Web App

This project is a simple staff HR web app connected to Google Sheets.

Main links

Web app:
https://yogurutotopssathupradit-creator.github.io/yg-hr/

Google Sheet:
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1IOAqxlOhbJrESNDzdkE5yd44sDGPJy9yD_u6UbOkCXE/edit?gid=463698880#gid=463698880

Apps Script Web App:
https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbxPwTQW5BL9yMZhbkCfe_br1CPU6mjBiw1nJ-1N3v6H1rDAlW1-0kEoEA32K9ohwIkcMg/exec


How it works

1. Staff open the web app on their phone.
2. The web app sends requests to Apps Script.
3. Apps Script reads and writes data in the Google Sheet.
4. The Google Sheet is the main database.


Where to edit data

Employee names:
Edit the "พนักงาน" tab.
Only rows with "ตำแหน่ง" set to "พนักงาน" will appear in the web app.

Check-in and check-out records:
Saved in the "เช็คอิน-เอาท์" tab.

Leave requests:
Saved in the "ลางาน" tab.
Admin can change the status in the sheet.

OT requests:
Saved in the "โอที" tab.
Admin can change the status in the sheet.

Schedule:
Edit the "ตารางกะ" tab.

Public holidays:
Edit the "วันหยุดนักขัตฤกษ์" tab.


Important rules

Do not rename sheet tabs unless the code is also updated.

When adding a new employee, make sure:
- Name is in the "ชื่อ" column.
- Position is exactly "พนักงาน".
- OT rate is filled in the "อัตราโอที/ชม." column.
- Day off is filled in the "วันหยุดประจำ" column.

If the employee does not appear in the web app, check that the position is exactly:
พนักงาน


When code changes

If index.html changes:
Push the file to GitHub so GitHub Pages updates the web app.

If Apps Script changes:
You must deploy a new Apps Script version.

Steps:
1. Open Apps Script.
2. Paste the updated Apps Script code.
3. Click Deploy > Manage deployments.
4. Edit the Web App deployment.
5. Choose New version.
6. Click Deploy.

Just clicking Run is not enough for the live web app.


Apps Script deployment settings

Execute as:
Me

Who has access:
Anyone

The Google Sheet itself can remain private. Apps Script is the public gate that the web app uses.


Security note

The app uses a shared secret token to block casual access to the Apps Script API.

This is basic protection only. A technical person could still inspect the web app code. For stronger protection, add employee PINs or Google login later.
